$interpreted: Naya: Fredrica!?
Theodore: General Lucien, you are late!
Fredrica: Well~ I thought your Majesty was having a good time acting~ I didn't want to barge in too early and ruin your fun...
Theodore: Does this count as evidence of your potential betrayal?
Fredrica: Just kidding. Everything your Majesty ordered has been set up perfectly!
Dagger: Angelia, a bunch soldiers suddenly appeared behind us!
Crushfang: They're on both sides. We're surrounded!
Angelia: What the...!? Sir Hyde told us...
Sione: They've turned our tricks on us.
Theodore: Pretending to have internal strife, then using this opportunity to capture me and have a chance at a fatal blow. That's the plan, isn't it?
Theodore: You were raised by me; what makes you think you could fool me? Every single soldier in the kingdom is here; let's see how you escape this time!
Fredrica: What a drag...can you guys just not resist and let me finish already? That way I can go home and get some time off.
Dylan: We are severely outnumbered...must retreat, now!
Sione: Colonel Levon, I'll stay behind and buy some time!
Sione: Please bring the princess and the remaining soldiers back to Sunshine Infantry; we can reorganize then!
Angelia: Sione!
Sione: Chieftain Crushfang!?
Crushfang: One human is not enough. I'll help you out.
Crushfang: Bears' elite, come with me!
Dagger: Stinkin old man!?
Crushfang: Bears' dignity has not been forgotten. Dagger, take care of the remaining Bear soldiers!
Fredrica: One after the other, stop wasting my time! Ugh, this is so annoying! None of you will get away!
Dylan: Everyone, retreat!
Angelia: NO! Wait!
Dylan: Princess, you've already made one mistake. Do not waste the efforts of Sione and Chieftain Crushfang!
Angelia: ......
Dylan: Alright everyone, we will fight our way out of this and return to Sunshine Infantry safely!
Naya: Damn it, too many people are falling behind!
Dylan: No time to go back for them. Everyone has only one destination. May the sun bless their souls...
Theodore: Don't you dare run from me!
Angelia: Guys !?
Dylan: Princess, take the remaining troops back. I'll hold off Theodore!
Dagger: Can't let Chieftain look down on me. Angelia, take care of Bear soldiers for now. I will return safely!
Theodore: You godforsaken bastards, how long are you going to interfere with my business!
Naya: Angel!
Angelia: Sunshine Infantry and fellow Bear soldiers, follow me and retreat to Totemtaff!
Hyde: Total and utter defeat...I expect no less from Theodore...
Angelia: Sir Hyde, you don't seem to be too surprised?

Hyde: The strategy itself is naive in nature, not to mention that our opponent saw right through the princess. 
I would be more surprised if we actually won.
Angelia: So you already knew we're going to lose, but you still...why!?
Naya: Angel, Dagger and Colonel Levon somehow made it back to the infantry!
Angelia: They made it back? Are they alright? What about others?
Naya: Seriously injured. Both of them are getting emergency treatment now.
Naya: But regarding dear Sione and Chieftain Crushfang...nothing...Best case scenario, captured alive by Theodore; worst case scenario...
Hyde: Princess, where do you think you're going?
Angelia: MOVE! I need to go see Dagger and Colonel Levon!
Hyde: Your presence will only create distractions. What you should do now is figure out your next step.
Naya: Angel!
Naya: HEY! Angel's just showing her concern. What the hell is wrong with you!?
Hyde: If being concerned is all you can do, then you have no right to be the leader of a kingdom!
Hyde: The value of a strategist lies in the hands of their commander. I can provide the strategies, but only you can make the final decisions.
Angelia: ...You're saying, that I am responsible for all this...
Hyde: When reducing casualties is your main priority instead of actually winning, the strategy you choose will always be incorrect.
Angelia: ......
Naya: Shut up will ya! You really want me to give you a good beating, do you!?
Angelia: ... No, Hyde is correct. I didn't have enough resolve to make the necessary decision...
Angelia: Must I become  heartless in order to win? Can we actually defeat Theodore?
Angelia: ... Please tell me the truth, Hyde.
Hyde: The path that awaits you is very tough...once you set foot on it, there is no turning back. You...will no longer be yourself.
